                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17291015-45-off215 t17291015-45-cd217"></join> last.</p>
               <p>The Prosecutor depos'd, that she went out to pay a Visit about 5 a-Clock in the Afternoon, the Day laid in the Indictment, and returning Home betwixt 8 and 9, could not get Entrance; whereupon her Footman went round about, and got in the Back Way, finding the Doors backward all open, and opening the Fore-Door, let her in, saying, Madam you are robb'd; that she going into her Rooms, found her Cabinet broken open, and the Drawers and Band-Boxes, &amp;c. all thrown about the Room, and the Goods and Money mention'd in the Indictment, gone, and finding her Servant. 
               <persName id="t17291015-45-person233">
                  Betty 
                  Loyd 
               <interp inst="t17291015-45-person233" type="surname" value="Loyd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-45-person233" type="given" value="Betty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-45-person233" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and examining her, she pretended to have been bound, and that the Robbery had been committed by two Persons, who she did believe were Men in Women's Cloaths; and that the Servants did not own for a considerable time who committed the Robbery.</p>
               <p>
            
