               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17291015-45-person248">
                  Sarah 
                  Bushy 
               <interp inst="t17291015-45-person248" type="surname" value="Bushy"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-45-person248" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-45-person248" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That she had known the Prisoner several Years, but had not seen her before for a Year or two; but accidentally meeting her that Day, she told her, she was coming out of Place, and ask'd her for a Lodging in an honest House, whereupon she offer'd her one in her own; that she soon after sent in the Trunk before-mentioned; that she knew not what was in it; that it was brought about 4 in the Afternoon, and fetch'd away by the same Porter, with the Constable, about 6, and carried to Madam Thorold's House, as it afterwards appear'd. The Fact being plainly prov'd, the Jury found her <rs id="t17291015-45-verdict218" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17291015-45-verdict218" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
